- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as lambda calculus is a core concept in functional programming languages. 
- cs.TL (Programming Languages Theory) is another possible category as the paper discusses the efficiency of lambda term reduction, which is a topic of interest in programming language theory. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may be of interest to software engineers who work with functional programming languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a less likely category, but the paper may be relevant to researchers working on algorithmic aspects of lambda calculus.
